For this memory game you need a brain the size of an elephant&rsquo;s to keep up with the animals who often move between hiding places... Be careful not to lose  track of them...

Dans ce jeu de m&eacute;mo, il faut une m&eacute;moire d&rsquo;&eacute;l&eacute;phant pour se souvenir de l&rsquo;emplacement des animaux qui changent souvent de cachette&hellip; Attention &agrave; ne pas perdre le fil&hellip;

&mdash;description from the publisher

Potlatch, the game, is a strategic, educational card game based on indigenous philosophies. It is designed to meet Washington's K-12 educational standards for teaching about native history, economics, culture, and government. The game was developed as a community effort with local elders and language experts. The game is written in both English and Lushootseed, the indigenous language of the Salish Pacific Northwest. Game mechanics are based on sharing resources to meet other players&rsquo; needs for food, materials, technology, and knowledge.

This is a collaborative game where there is not one winner. Success is determined by whether or not all houses have their resource needs met by the end of the game.

The game is named for the Potlatch, which is a ceremonial distribution and re-distribution of resources, property, food, knowledge, and wealth with the purpose of affirming social status via the historic economic systems of subsistence, prestige, and sharing. Potlatching is practiced by indigenous peoples of the Pacific NW coast of the U.S. and Canada. Historically it supported a large socio-economic system to maintain a high level of food production and to equalize food accessibility. Individuals, families, or communities host potlatches and planning takes a year or more. Skagit elder and historian, Vi Hilbert, wrote &ldquo;Public acts of distributing valuables to guests were the ultimate confirmation of a host&rsquo;s achievements and personal high-status in their family and community.&rdquo;

Your investigations have led you far from that fateful first showing of The King in Yellow at the Ward Theatre in Arkham. When you could no longer find the answers you needed in Arkham, you voyaged across the Atlantic to France and entered the catacombs of the dead beneath Paris. Now, you travel to the island commune of Mont Saint-Michel, as brooding, dark clouds cover the sky. A storm is coming&mdash;and it&rsquo;s unclear if our world will survive.

Black Stars Rise offers the latest chapter in The Path to Carcosa cycle, and the latest tale of your own madness. You have looked upon the face of the Stranger. You have beheld the Pallid Mask and the Tattered Cloak. New player cards arrive in this Mythos Pack, cards with palliative names like &ldquo;Stick to the Plan,&rdquo; &ldquo;Narrow Escape,&rdquo; or &ldquo;Ward of Protection.&rdquo; Their names are a lie, dripping with false comfort that only the truly mad will embrace. The darkling spires of Carcosa are breaching the walls between dimensions and Hastur will rule over all&hellip;

&mdash;description from the publisher

Violent winds of Keldon prophecy threaten to bring about the end of Dominara, but the mana-rich lands of Jamuraa are far from defenseless. As powerful factions clash, giant Avatars fight by your side, and Rhystic spells give you more than you pay for &hellip;

This 143-card set includes randomly inserted foil premium cards and features new mechanics like Wind spells, giant Avatars, and Rhystic spells.

&mdash;description from the publisher

The ancient Planeswalker Urza continues to wage war across Dominaria. Will he achieve his ultimate goal, ending the Phyrexian&rsquo;s reign of terror forever? Urza&rsquo;s final conflict is here. What will be his&mdash;and Dominaria&rsquo;s&mdash;destiny? That&rsquo;s up to you &hellip;

This 143-card set includes randomly inserted foil premium cards. It&rsquo;s the third and final set in the Urza block, which features new mechanics like Cycling, Echo, Sleeping Enchantments, and Growing Enchantments.

&mdash;description from the publisher

The Planeshift has come, and the Phyrexians are taking no prisoners. Wield low-cost monstrosities that return an ally to your hand, creatures that reduce the costs of all your spells, tricolor mana Dragon Lairs, and double-Kicker Battlemages. Two worlds. Many ways to die. Will you survive?

This 143-card, black-bordered set features the mechanics of the Invasion block and cycles of Familiars, Battlemages, and &ldquo;Dragon Lairs.&rdquo;

&mdash;description from the publisher

Arbosh had driven Carolan into a corner and gotten ready to take him out with a huge blow of his Ox-Herd when he realized to his surprise that he wasn&rsquo;t holding the weapon in his hand. &ldquo;Are you looking for this?&rdquo; said Carolan, triumphantly raising the stolen weapon over his head.

&ldquo;You disgusting little thief!&rdquo; Arbosh spat out and reached into his backpack with an annoyed grunt...and pulled out another Ox-Herd from it! &ldquo;Luckily, I always go with two of them these days,&rdquo; he added with a grim smile. &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s see which of us is better at wielding it!&rdquo;

Surprise your opponents with completely new decks! Arsenal of Heroes is a duel expansion for Aventuria - the Adventure Card Game, dedicated to deck customization and tournament play. It includes rules for running tournaments, deck strategies, and extra cards to fill out your Base Set so that you have at least two of every card!

"Aventuria - Duellerweiterung Arsenal der Helden"
Arbosch hatte Carolan in die Ecke gedr&auml;ngt, holte zu einem gewaltigen Schlag mit seiner Ochsenherde aus - und stellte &uuml;berrascht fest, dass er das gute St&uuml;ck nicht mehr in der Hand hielt. &bdquo;Suchst du das hier?&ldquo;, sagte Carolan, die erbeutete Waffe triumphierend in die H&ouml;he gereckt. &bdquo;Du widerlicher kleiner Dieb!&ldquo;, spuckte Arbosch aus, griff mit einem &auml;rgerlichen Grunzen in seinen Rucksack ... und zog eine weitere Ochsenherde hervor! &bdquo;Zum Gl&uuml;ck habe ich jetzt immer zwei dabei&ldquo;, f&uuml;gte er mit einem grimmigen L&auml;cheln hinzu. &bdquo;Mal sehen, wer von uns besser damit umgehen kann!&ldquo;

&Uuml;berrasche deine Gegner mit v&ouml;llig neuen Decks! Arsenal der Helden ist eine Duellerweiterung f&uuml;r Aventuria - Das Abenteuerkartenspiel, die dir genug Karten zur Verf&uuml;gung stellt, um alle denkbaren Deck-Kombinationen aus der Grundbox zu spielen.

Dominaria lies in ruins once again, but this time, the damage is more than skin deep. Strange storms bring flashes of an ancient past. Unlikely allies band together to heal the land&mdash;but what they discover will change all the planes forever &hellip;

Time Spiral features 301 cards, plus 121 special "timeshifted" reprint cards from Magic past.

&mdash;description from the publisher

The time rifts that are tearing Dominaria apart have reached into the future, and what comes spilling out is wholly unexpected. Phyrexian horrors flood Dominaria through a rift in time. Planeswalker allies band together to help&mdash;some even sacrificing themselves. Meanwhile, a secret evil may destroy all their valiant efforts &hellip;

The third and final set in the Time Spiral block, Future Sight features 180 cards, including 81 with a frame treatment from an alternative future timeline, and randomly inserted premium cards. Some &ldquo;timeshifted&rdquo; cards from this set have appeared in later expansions.

&mdash;description from the publisher

The idyllic twilight of Lorywn is now the eerie eternal night of Shadowmoor. The gloom has seeped into the plane&rsquo;s inhabitants, too, transforming creatures of fable into malicious monsters. The races and characters you know from Lorwyn are back, but with twisted allegiances and dark new powers. Even the new game mechanics are warped &hellip;

This 301-card expansion set features randomly inserted premium cards, mono-colored hybrid cards, and four new game mechanics: Wither, Persist, Untap, and Conspire.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Necromunda: Underhive contains a number of Tactics cards, which can be used to represent the myriad tricks and schemes employed by the gangs. Expand your games of Necromunda: Underhive &ndash; whichever gang you play &ndash; with this set of 26 extra cards. Included:


     8 Goliath Tactics cards, which are for the exclusive use of the Goliath gang;
     12 Gang Tactics cards, which can be used by any gang in Necromunda: Underhive;
     6 blank Fighter cards &ndash; perfect for the Champions and Leaders in your gang deck, these have been stamped with the House Goliath crest. 


